PREAMBLE
This is not a joke. This is not a suggestion. This is a declaration.

I, fevber, have invested significant time, effort, brainpower, late nights, caffeine consumption, and sheer willpower into creating this work. This is not some random code I copied from Stack Overflow and rearranged. This is my original work, crafted for my academic purposes, and it represents my understanding, my creativity, and my dedication to my education.

I am sharing this work only because I am required to submit it for academic evaluation. I am not sharing it so that others can copy it, modify it, repurpose it, or claim it as their own. I am not sharing it to be generous. I am not sharing it to be helpful. I am sharing it because I have to.

If you are reading this, you are either:

(a) My teacher, evaluating my work — in which case, welcome, please be kind;

(b) A fellow student who found this and is considering using it — in which case, stop reading and walk away; or

(c) Someone who stumbled upon this by accident — in which case, feel free to admire it from a distance, but do not touch.

This declaration exists to make one thing absolutely clear: This is mine. Not yours. Mine.

ARTICLE I — THE WORK
1.1 Definition of "The Work"
For the purposes of this declaration, "The Work" shall mean:
All source code files, scripts, programs, and applications contained in this repository or submission;
All documentation, comments, explanations, and written materials accompanying the code;
All design assets, graphics, images, diagrams, and visual elements;
All data structures, algorithms, logic, and methodologies implemented in the code;
All original ideas, concepts, and approaches reflected in the Work;
Any and all files, content, or materials that are part of this submission;
Any derivative, adaptation, translation, modification, or extension of the foregoing;
Any output, results, logs, or data generated by the Work;
Any intellectual property, creative expression, or academic contribution embodied in the Work.

1.2 Originality Statement
I hereby declare and affirm that The Work is my own original creation. I have not copied it from any other source without proper attribution. I have not used unauthorized assistance. I have not plagiarized. I have not stolen. I have not cheated. This Work represents my own efforts, my own learning, and my own academic integrity.

1.3 Moral Claim
Beyond any legal or institutional framework, I claim moral ownership of this Work. This is not just code — this is my time, my struggle, my frustration, my breakthroughs, my late nights staring at a screen wondering why it wouldn't compile, and my triumph when it finally worked. You cannot steal that. You cannot replicate that. And you will not take credit for it.

ARTICLE II
2.1 For My Teacher
If you are my teacher:
You are permitted to read, review, evaluate, and grade The Work.
You are permitted to test, run, and examine The Work to assess its functionality.
You are permitted to provide feedback, corrections, and suggestions.
You are permitted to share The Work with other teaching staff for evaluation purposes.
You are permitted to keep copies for academic records and accreditation purposes.
You are NOT permitted to share The Work with other students, either current or future, without my explicit consent.
You are NOT permitted to use The Work as a teaching example without my explicit consent.
You are NOT permitted to distribute The Work beyond the scope of this class.

2.2 For Me
I am permitted to:

Do whatever I want with my own work, obviously. It's mine.

2.3 others
If you are not me and not my teacher:
You are permitted to look at The Work for inspiration. That's it.
You are NOT permitted to copy, paste, reuse, or incorporate any part of The Work into your own submissions.
You are NOT permitted to modify, adapt, or change The Work in any way.
You are NOT permitted to share, distribute, or upload The Work anywhere.
You are NOT permitted to claim any ownership or authorship of The Work.
You are NOT permitted to use The Work for any purpose without my explicit, written, and revocable consent.
You are NOT permitted to submit The Work as your own — that's plagiarism, and you know it.
You are NOT permitted to use The Work to complete any assignment, project, or task that is not your own.

ARTICLE III 
You are strictly, absolutely, unequivocally, and unconditionally prohibited from doing any of the following:

3.1 Copying
Copying, duplicating, replicating, cloning, or reproducing The Work in whole or in part;
Copying any code, function, class, method, variable, algorithm, or logic from The Work;
Copying any documentation, comments, explanations, or written content from The Work;
Copying any design, layout, structure, or visual element from The Work;
Copying any concept, approach, technique, or methodology from The Work;
Using any portion of The Work as a template, model, or starting point for your own work;
Using any portion of The Work to complete, supplement, or enhance your own work.

3.2 Submission
Submitting The Work, or any portion thereof, as your own work for any academic purpose;
Submitting The Work, or any portion thereof, to any teacher, class, assignment, or course;
Submitting The Work, or any portion thereof, to any competition, publication, or other forum;
Submitting The Work, or any portion thereof, as part of any portfolio, resume, or application;
Submitting The Work, or any portion thereof, for any credit, grade, mark, or recognition;
Submitting any work that is substantially similar to, derived from, or inspired by The Work, without my explicit consent.

3.3 Sharing
Sharing, distributing, transmitting, or disseminating The Work to any person, group, or entity;
Uploading The Work to any website, repository, platform, cloud service, or shared location;
Posting The Work on any forum, social media, chat, or messaging platform;
Emailing, messaging, or otherwise sending The Work to anyone;
Making The Work available for download, access, or use by anyone else;
Discussing The Work's content, code, or approach in any way that would enable others to replicate it.

3.4 Modification
Modifying, altering, adapting, translating, or changing The Work in any way;
Refactoring, restructuring, or reorganizing The Work;
Optimizing, improving, or enhancing The Work;
Fixing, patching, or correcting any perceived errors or bugs in The Work;
Adding, removing, or changing any file, line, comment, or character of The Work;
Creating any derivative work, adaptation, translation, port, fork, or variant of The Work;
Combining, integrating, or merging The Work with any other code, project, or material.

3.5 Claiming
Claiming ownership, authorship, credit, or responsibility for The Work;
Claiming that The Work is your own creation;
Removing, altering, or obscuring any attribution, credit, or identification of me as the author;
Adding your name, your copyright, your license, or your credit to The Work;
Implying, suggesting, or representing that I endorsed, approved, or collaborated with you;
Using my name, my work, or any associated material without my explicit consent.

3.6 Misuse
Using The Work for any purpose that is dishonest, unethical, or academically improper;
Using The Work to cheat, plagiarize, deceive, or gain unfair advantage;
Using The Work to facilitate, enable, or assist any violation of academic integrity policies;
Using The Work in any way that violates my rights, my reputation, or my interests;
Using The Work in any way that harms, damages, or undermines my academic standing;
Using The Work in any way that is illegal, harmful, malicious, or unethical.

ARTICLE IV — CONSEQUENCES (WHAT HAPPENS IF YOU VIOLATE THIS)

4.1 First Violation
If I discover that you have violated any provision of this declaration, I will:
Document the violation with evidence;
Confront you directly, in person, and demand an explanation;
Require you to immediately cease all use of The Work and permanently delete any copies;
Report the incident to the relevant teacher, professor, or academic authority;
Share with them all evidence of the violation;
Request that you receive a zero (0) or failing grade for the assignment in question;
Request that you face appropriate academic consequences, including but not limited to:
Academic warning;
Formal reprimand;
Grade penalty;
Course failure;
Academic probation;
Referral to academic integrity committee;
Ineligibility for awards or honors;
Any other disciplinary action deemed appropriate by the institution.

4.2 Second Violation
If I discover that you have violated this declaration a second time, after having been warned once, I will:
Escalate the matter to the highest appropriate academic authority;
Request the most severe penalties available under institutional policy;
Seek to have you permanently recorded as an academic integrity violator;
Consider public disclosure of the violation (within appropriate boundaries);
Refuse to ever work with you, collaborate with you, or assist you in any way;
Warn others in my academic network about your behavior.

4.3 Aggravating Circumstances
The following circumstances will result in even more severe consequences:
If you attempt to pass my work off as your own to a teacher;
If you use my work to complete a major assignment, exam, or thesis;
If you share my work with multiple other students, enabling a widespread cheating ring;
If you attempt to remove my name, comments, or identifying information from The Work;
If you claim that The Work is your original creation in any formal or official capacity;
If you use my work for commercial, professional, or competitive purposes without my consent.
4.4 What I Will NOT Do
To be absolutely clear: I will not sue you. I will not bring legal action against you. I will not demand money from you. I will not involve lawyers. I will not pursue criminal charges. I will not try to bankrupt you or ruin your life.

I am a student, just like you (mostly).
I don't want to be in court.
I don't want money from you.
I don't want to destroy your future.
I want you to respect my work and not cheat off me.

4.5 What This Means
The consequences of violating this declaration are:

Academic: You will fail the assignment. You may fail the course. Your academic record may be permanently marked.
Social: I will know you are a cheater. Others will know. Your reputation will suffer.
Personal: You will have to live with the knowledge that you stole someone else's work and got caught. That feels terrible. Don't do it.

ARTICLE V 

5.1 Why This Declaration Exists
This declaration exists because plagiarism is wrong. Academic dishonesty is wrong. Taking credit for someone else's work is wrong. Cheating yourself out of an education is wrong.
I spent time on this. I struggled. I learned. I grew. That is the point of education — not the grade, not the credential, but the learning.
If you copy my work, you are not learning. You are depriving yourself of the opportunity to grow. You are also depriving me of the recognition I earned.

5.2 Academic Integrity
I believe in academic integrity. I have followed the rules. I have done my own work. I expect the same from you.
If you are struggling with your assignment, ask for help. Go to office hours. Talk to your teacher. Work with a tutor. Put in the effort. Do not copy my work.

5.3 A Note to Fellow Students
I know school is hard. I know you're stressed. I know you have other classes, other obligations, other pressures. I get it. Truly.
But copying is not the answer. You will feel worse in the long run. You will not have learned anything. You will have cheated yourself. And you will have betrayed my trust.
Just do your own work. It's better for everyone.

5.4 A Note to My Teacher
If you are reading this, thank you for taking the time to understand my perspective. I have worked hard on this project, and I am proud of it. I hope you appreciate the effort I put in, and I hope you understand why I feel strongly about protecting my work.

If another student submits work that is substantially similar to mine, I trust that you will take appropriate action. I am not asking for anything unreasonable — I am simply asking for fairness.

ARTICLE VI — MISCELLANEOUS PROVISIONS
6.1 Entire Agreement
This declaration constitutes the entire agreement between me (fevberr) and any reader regarding The Work. It supersedes any prior or contemporaneous understandings, communications, or representations.

6.2 Severability
If any provision of this declaration is held to be invalid, unenforceable, or otherwise ineffective, the remaining provisions shall remain in full force and effect.

6.3 No Waiver
My failure to enforce any provision of this declaration shall not constitute a waiver of that provision or of my right to enforce it later.

6.4 Amendments
This declaration may not be amended, modified, or supplemented except by a written document signed by me.

6.5 Governing Principles
This declaration is governed by the principles of:
Academic integrity;
Fairness;
Respect for others' work;
Personal responsibility;
Honesty and transparency.

6.6 Effective Date
This declaration is effective immediately upon your reading of it.

6.7 Duration
This declaration shall remain in effect indefinitely, permanently, and forever, or until I choose to revoke it (which I probably won't).

ARTICLE VII — ACKNOWLEDGMENT

7.1 By Accessing This Work
By accessing, viewing, downloading, reading, or otherwise interacting with The Work, you acknowledge that:
You have read this entire declaration;
You understand this entire declaration;
You agree to be bound by this entire declaration;
You will comply with every provision of this declaration;
You accept all risks and responsibilities associated with accessing The Work;
You waive any claim that you did not understand, were not aware of, or were not given adequate notice of this declaration.

7.2 If You Do Not Agree
If you do not agree to every single provision of this declaration:
Immediately cease all access to The Work;
Do not download, copy, or interact with The Work in any way;
Delete any copies you may have inadvertently obtained;
Do not use any information or knowledge you may have gained from The Work.

FINAL STATEMENT
This is my work. I made it. I own it. I worked hard for it.
I am sharing it because I have to, not because I want to. I am protecting it because I have to, not because I want to. I am writing this long, serious, intimidating declaration because I want to make it absolutely, incontrovertibly, crystal-clear that this is not for you to take.
Do not copy it. Do not steal it. Do not modify it. Do not claim it. Do not share it.
If you want to do your own project, do your own work. If you need help, ask your teacher. If you're stuck, try harder. If you're desperate, ask for an extension. If you're tempted to cheat, don't.
I will know if you copy this. Maybe not immediately. Maybe not obviously. But I will find out. And when I do, I will not be nice about it.
Be better than that. Do your own work.

THE WORK IS PROVIDED "AS IS" — I AM NOT RESPONSIBLE FOR ANYTHING THAT HAPPENS AS A RESULT OF YOUR USE, MISUSE, OR INABILITY TO USE THE WORK. USE IT AT YOUR OWN RISK. I'M NOT YOUR TECH SUPPORT.

